# Complexity
>- Time complexity: Here the complexity would be $O(n^2)$ as we can see that we need a 2d looping for the management of memoization using the length so $O(n^2)$.

>- Space complexity: Here We can clearly see that we need a 2D dp so the space complexity will also be $O(n^2)$ and which can be further optimised to $O(n)$ by using space optimisation in Dp as the final states and previous states differ by one index.


