solutions.content:
**Intution from recursion to DP**
So question is to match the two string where one contain some special character having some meaning ,
ok let's start thinking from basic if have two string to comapre what we can do:-
* compare first letter from both if equal then recursively compare for next letter , if not equal then simply return false.
* Base conditions:  
1. * if both string exhaust return true.    
1. * if one string exhaust and one is still , return false.

Now come to our question we have two special char.
1. '?' replacable by any single letter
2. '*' replaceable by 0 or more letters.

Thus we need to consider three cases :-
1. when we encouter '*' in our pattern string , so we will recursively take all possibility like from empty string to the whole remaining string in our string .
2. when we encounter '? in our pattern string , simply we insert the same char which is present in our string, thus we move for the next.
3. same as normal check if current char are equal && recursively call for next char.

#### **Here is sample code for it.**

```
 bool rec(string s, string p,int i,int j){
        if(s.length() == i && p.length() == j) return true;
        if(s.length() == i) {
            while(j != p.length()){
                if(p[j] != '*') return false;
                j++;
            }
            return true;
        }
        if(p.length() == j) return false;

        if(p[j] == '*'){ 
            int k = i;
            bool ans = false;
            while(s.length() >= k){
                ans = ans  | rec(s,p,k,j+1);
                k++;
            }
            return ans;
        }
        else if(p[j] == '?'){
            return rec(s,p,i+1,j+1);
        }
        else{
           return s[i] == p[j] && rec(s,p,i+1,j+1);
        }
    }
```

But In this question it give TLE for the provided input , so we need to go for DP
In Dp intialision part will be like if string length 0 so only if pattern contains * then true otherwise false,
and if pattern length 0 ,not possible so always false.
if encounter '*' look for one less in first || one less in seocond , '?' look for one less in both
otherwise normally comapre and look for one less in both.

### **Here is DP working code**

```
   bool isMatch(string s, string p) {
        int n = s.length();
        int m = p.length();

        bool dp[n+1][m+1];
        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<=m;j++){
                //initalisation
                if(i == 0 && j == 0) dp[i][j] = true;
                if(i == 0 && j > 0){
                    dp[i][j] = (p[j-1] == '*') && dp[i][j-1];
                }
                if(i > 0 && j == 0) dp[i][j] = false;
                if(i > 0 && j > 0){
                    if(p[j-1] == '*'){
                        dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j] || dp[i][j-1];
                    }
                    else if(p[j-1] == '?'){
                        dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1];
                    }
                    else{
                        dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] && (s[i-1] == p[j-1]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return dp[n][m];
   }
```

But if we consider complexity of solution it's like :-
1. Time Comlexity O(n*m)
2. space Comlexity O(n*m)

We can do better ? using two pointer approach.
[Explanation](https://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/17811/My-three-C%2B%2B-solutions-(iterative-(16ms)-and-DP-(180ms)-and-modified-recursion-(88ms)))

```
  bool isMatch(string s, string p) {
        int  n = s.size();
        int  m = p.size();
        int k =-1,jEnc=-1;
        int i=0,j=0;
        while(i < n){
            if(p[j]=='*'){ 
                k   = i;
                jEnc = j;
                i--;
            }
            else{ 
                if(p[j] != s[i] && p[j] != '?'){
                    if(k >=0){
                        i = k;
                        j = jEnc;
                        k++;
                    }
                    else return false; 
                }
            }
            ++i;
            ++j;
        }

        while(p[j]=='*') ++j;
        return j == m;
    }
```

credit to [Lejas](https://leetcode.com/LeJas/) for explaining two pointer solution in [this post.](https://leetcode.com/problems/wildcard-matching/discuss/17811/My-three-C%2B%2B-solutions-(iterative-(16ms)-and-DP-(180ms)-and-modified-recursion-(88ms)))

