solutions.content:
# Intuition
There are two cases we can encounter
- pattern[i]==string[j] or pattern[i]=='?' this is normal case and we can just move onto next index
- pattern[i]=='\*' when it is '\*' we need to further check two other cases
   - '*'can mean it matches with nothing
   - or it matches whith a sequence
- The two cases can be calculated recursively as 
```helper(s,p,dp,si,pi-1)|| helper(s,p,dp,si-1,pi);```
- Here when it matches with nothing the index of string remains the same and pattern is reduced as it matches nothing
- In second case we keep the pattern index at the same position ('*')
and reduce the string index as we need to check if it matches further and this recursio covers all cases
- Ther recursion values are stored in a vector(memoisation) which improves the time complexity
- Further a cleanup function was created to remove multiple '*' placed together in the pattern as 'ab\***cd' pattern is same as 'ab\*cd' which reduces calculation time

# Approach
- cleanup function created which removes duplicate * and returns cleaned pattern
- BASE CASES
    - ```if(pi<0 && si<0)```: return true as both patten and word is empty
    - ```else if(pi<0 &&si>=0)```: returns fasle as pattern is empty but word is not
    - ```else if(pi<0 &&si>=0)```: if pattern is empty further checks if pattern contains '*' only or not. If not then return false
- ```else if (dp[pi][si]!=-1)```: checks if dp has calculated the recursion call or not
- ```else if(p[pi]==s[si] || p[pi]=='?')```: Case 1 where we reduce both indexes by ```helper(s,p,dp,si-1,pi-1);```
- ```else if(p[pi]=='*')```: checks both cases as mentioned in the intuition by ```helper(s,p,dp,si,pi-1)|| helper(s,p,dp,si-1,pi);```

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(M*N) M,N is the length of string and pattern 

- Space complexity:
O(M*N)+O(M+N) .O(M+N) is the auxillary stack space

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string cleanup(string p) {
        string cleaned_str = "";
        for (int i = 0; i < p.size(); i++) {
            if (cleaned_str.empty() || p[i] != '*') {
                cleaned_str.append(1, p[i]);
            } else if (i >= 1 && cleaned_str[cleaned_str.size() - 1] != '*') {
                cleaned_str.append(1, p[i]);
            }
        }
        return cleaned_str;
    }

    bool helper(string &s, string &p, vector<vector<int>>&dp,int si,int pi) {
        if(pi<0 && si<0){
            return true;
        }
        else if(pi<0 &&si>=0){
            return false;
        }
        else if(pi>=0 && si<0){
            for(int k=0;k<=pi;k++){
                if(p[k]!='*') return false;
            }
            return true;
        }
        else if (dp[pi][si]!=-1) {
            return dp[pi][si];
        }
        else if(p[pi]==s[si] || p[pi]=='?'){
            return dp[pi][si]=helper(s,p,dp,si-1,pi-1);
        }
        else if(p[pi]=='*'){
            return dp[pi][si]= helper(s,p,dp,si,pi-1)|| helper(s,p,dp,si-1,pi);
        }

        return dp[pi][si]=false;
    }

    bool isMatch(string s, string p) {
        if (p != "") {
            p = cleanup(p);
        }
        int m=s.size();
        int n=p.size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n,vector<int>(m,-1));
        return helper(s, p, dp,m-1,n-1);
    }
};

```

