solutions.content:
My idea is to split pattern into multiple sub-patterns by '*'.
For example:
```
p        sub-patterns
""    -> []
"a"   -> ["a"]
"a*b" -> ["a", "b"]
"*a"  -> ["", "a"]
"a*"  -> ["a", ""]
"*a*" -> ["", "a", ""]
"*"   -> ["", ""]
"**"  -> ["", "", ""]
```
Then search those sub-patterns in the string. String is matched when:
```text
if (sub-patterns == []) only empty string can be matched.
if (sub-patterns.size() == 1) string must be strictly matched.
if (sub-patterns.size() >= 2) {
    string must match the fist sub-pattern from start. &&
	string must match the last sub-pattern at end. &&
	middle sub-patterns can be matched by order.
}
```
Complexity:
```
space: O(p.length)
 time: O(s.length * p.length) for worst scenario
```
Show code:
```
class Solution {
    public boolean isMatch(String s, String p) {
        int slen = s.length();
        List<String> parts = split(p.toCharArray());
        if (parts.isEmpty()) return slen == 0;

        // handle first
        String firstP = parts.get(0);
        if (!match(s, 0, firstP)) return false;
        if (parts.size() == 1) return slen == firstP.length();

        int si = firstP.length();

        // handle middle
        FOR_PARTS:
        for (int i = 1; i < parts.size() - 1; ++i) {
            String currP = parts.get(i);
            while (si <= slen) {
                if (match(s, si, currP)) {
                    si += currP.length();
                    continue FOR_PARTS;
                }
                ++si;
            }
            return false;
        }

        // handle last
        String lastP = parts.get(parts.size()-1);
        int lastSlen = slen - si;
        if (lastSlen < lastP.length()) return false;
        si = slen - lastP.length();
        return match(s, si, lastP);
    }

    private boolean match(String s, int si, String p) {
        int plen = p.length();
        int slen = s.length() - si;
        if (plen == 0) return true;
        if (slen < plen) return false;
        for (int i = 0; i < plen; ++i) {
            if (p.charAt(i) == '?') continue;
            if (s.charAt(si+i) != p.charAt(i)) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }

    // [] -> p is empty
    // ["s1"] -> p has no '*'
    // ["s1", "s2"] -> p has one '*'
    // ["", "s1"] -> p has '*' ahead
    // ["s1", ""] -> p has '*' at end
    // ["", ""] -> p == '*'
    private List<String> split(char[] p) {
        List<String> parts = new ArrayList<>();
        if (p.length > 0) {
            StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            for (char c : p) {
                if (c != '*') {
                    sb.append(c);
                } else {
                    parts.add(sb.toString());
                    sb = new StringBuilder();
                }
            }
            parts.add(sb.toString());
        }
        return parts;
    }
}
```

