# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Preorder Traversal of a binary tree, follows the order 
```
Traverse:
1.(root)         //Current Root
2.(root->left)   //Current Root's left
3.(root->right)  //Current Root's right
```
# Method 1 : Using Recursion
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> ans;    //Answer vector
    void pre(TreeNode * root){
        if(root==NULL) return ;
        else {
            ans.push_back(root->val);   //Take current root value.
            pre(root->left);            //Traverse root's Left
            pre(root->right);           //Traverse root's Right
        }
    }
    vector<int> preorderTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
        pre(root);    //Passing root for computation of recursive fn
        return ans;   //Final ans
    }

};
```
```
Time Complexity - O(N) //Traversing all nodes
Space Complexity- O(N) //Recursive Function calls
```
# Method 2 : Using Stack
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> preorderTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
        vector<int> pre;
        if(root==NULL) return pre;  //Empty Tree
        stack<TreeNode *> st;
        st.push(root);  //Push root
        while(!st.empty()){
            root=st.top();  //New root=Take the topmost node
            st.pop();       //Remove from stack
            pre.push_back(root->val);  //Push into ans vector
            if(root->right!=NULL) st.push(root->right);  //Goto Left 
            if(root->left!=NULL ) st.push(root->left);   //Goto Right
        }
        return pre;
    }
};
```
```
Time Complexity - O(N) //Traversing all nodes
Space Complexity- O(N) //Storing all nodes
```
