# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- ***Preorder Traversal is :  Root -> left-subtree -> right-subtree***

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- ### Recursive:
    1. Add the current root node to ans list
    2. Call preorder for the left subtree
    3. Call preorder for right subtree
    4. Base Case: If root is null just return.

- ### Iterative:
    1. If the root is null return an empty list
    2. Create a stack which will hold nodes of the tree.
    3. Push the root onto the stack
    4. Now iterate till stack is not empty
    5. At every iteration do the following: 
        a.  Pop the top node in stack and add it to ans list.
        b.  If we have a node to the right of the popped node, push it onto the stack;
        c.  If we have a left node add it to the stack too.


# Code 
## Recursive Approach
```
// Recursive Solution
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> preorderTraversal(TreeNode root) {
        List<Integer> ls = new ArrayList<>();
        preorder(root, ls);
        return ls;
    }
    public void preorder(TreeNode root, List<Integer> ls){
        if(root == null) return;

        ls.add(root.val);
        preorder(root.left, ls);
        preorder(root.right, ls);

    }
}
```
## Iterative Approach
``` 
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> preorderTraversal(TreeNode root) {
        List<Integer> ls = new ArrayList<>();
        if(root == null) return ls;

        Stack<TreeNode> st = new Stack<>();
        st.push(root);
        while(!st.empty()){
            TreeNode temp = st.pop();
            ls.add(temp.val);
            if(temp.right != null) st.push(temp.right);
            if(temp.left != null) st.push(temp.left);
        }
        return ls;
    } 
}
```

