Two pointers is the use of two different pointers (usually to keep track of array or string indexes) to solve a problem with specified indexes in order to save time and space.

To solve this problem, we just need to steps by indices from both ends, and swap them until the indices meet in the middle.

I hope the picture below will give you a clearer understanding :)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/f8dfebd6-5f46-4ffa-8071-7b4d0c6c94ba_1665314490.753274.png)


```
var reverseString = function(s) {
    for (let i = 0, j = s.length - 1; i < j;) {
        [s[i], s[j]] = [s[j], s[i]];
        i++;
        j--;
    }
    return s;
};
```

