Thought I could explain both iterative and the recursive solution here. The iterative solution is straight-forward since we want to run to the mid of the array swapping the start and the end of the array. Here is the code for that.

```
private void iterative(char[] s) {
	int i = 0;
	int j = s.length-1;
	while(i < j) {
		char temp = s[i];
		s[i] = s[j];
		s[j] = temp;
		i++;
		j--;
	}        
}
```

The recursive solution may be slightly tricky if we don't the follow the similar path as above. The idea is is to traverse to the mid of the array by incrementing the start and decreasing the end and swapping all the way.




    private void recursive(char[] arr, int s, int e) {
        if (s >= e) {
            return;
        }
        recursive(arr,s+1, e-1);
        char temp = arr[e];
        arr[e] = arr[s];
        arr[s] = temp;
    }

