# Intuition
Easy to understand and two pointer approach.

# Approach
A simple approach to run a loop which runs for n/2 times and for each iteration their is a swapping take place between the ith index  element and the element at (n-i-1)th index element.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
o(n)

- Space complexity:
o(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    void reverseString(vector<char>& s) {
        for(int i=0;i<s.size()/2;i++){
            swap(s[i],s[s.size()-i-1]);
        }
    }
};
```

