Problem is similar to [287. Find the Duplicate Number](https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-duplicate-number/).

```
Mark the element of nums[i] index in array to negative. When the duplicate value comes nums[nums[i]] will
be a negative value and we can find it. Also mis value = Sum(1:n) - Sum(nums) + duplicate value
```

```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findErrorNums(vector<int>& nums) {

        int n = nums.size();
        int t_sum = (n * (n+1))/2;
        int a_sum = 0;
        int dup;
        int mis;

        //check if nums[nums[i]] is negative, if then nums[i] is the duplicate value
        // in each step also mark nums[nums[i]] as negative value
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            a_sum+=abs(nums[i]);
            if(nums[abs(nums[i])-1]<0)dup = abs(nums[i]);
            nums[abs(nums[i])-1] = -1 * nums[abs(nums[i])-1];
        }

        mis = t_sum - a_sum + dup;
        return {dup,mis};
    }
};
```

