If we sort the nums[], and loop through it, we can find the duplicate and assign to `result[0]`. Then we loop through the expected numbers set, i.e., i belongs to `[1, nums.length]`, and find the missed when `nums[ni] != i && nums[ni + 1] != i`, and assign to `result[1]`.

