# Intuition
As this problems says about repetition, we should use mapping.

# Approach
As array contains elements from 1 to n only, we don't need extra spaced map. Instead we can use given array as map.

For example, 
n = 8
elements = [3,1,4,5,3,8,6,7]

If we have to mark 3 as visited we will make element at position (3-1) = 2 as visited.

So we will get modified array as
[3,1,-4,5,3,8,6,7]

Finally after all operations array will be

[-3,1,-4,-5-,3,-8,-6,-7]

While processing array, 3 is encountered twice. While processing duplicated 3, element at 2nd position is already marked. So this gives duplicated element.

We are getting 2nd element is unmakred this gives the element which is missing. That is 2 here. 

So ans is [3,2].

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findErrorNums(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int>ans;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int z = abs(nums[i]) - 1;
            if(nums[z]<0)
                ans.push_back(z+1);
            else
                nums[z] *= -1;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]>0){
                ans.push_back(i+1);break;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

