solutions.content:
For my first approach I went directly with a trie base solution for the prefix and a normal comparison for the suffix.

I created a `Trie` `struct` that contains 3 properties:
* `pos` is the position of a word in the initial input, defaulted to `-1` for all the nodes which are not word ends;
* `fullWord` is the full string that can be completed up to this node, defaulted to `""` for all the nodes which are not word ends;
* `children` is an array of `26` possible nodes that descent from the current node, one for each lowercase letter in the alphabet.

In our class we will then proceed to declare 3 class variables:
* `root` and `curr` are `Trie` pointers, with the first one initialised to be an empty node;
* `res` is going to be our support variable later on, when we will make calls to explore our `Trie` structure with DFS calls.

In our constructor we will then proceed to populate our `Trie` starting from `root`, using `curr` as a pointer while we go down the graph to describe each word and marking the last node with proper values for the `pos` and `fullWord` properties.

In the `f` method we will navigate our `Trie` again using `curr` as a pointer, going through each character `c` of `prefix`.

Once done, we will then call `dfs` passing both `curr` and `suffix` to check for each valid match; this function will do 2 simple things:
* check if the current node `root` is a end of word node and if said word can match the `suffix`, and in case update `res` accordingly, with the higher between its current value and `root->pos`;
* call itself recursively with each existing `child` in `root->children`, again passing just that and `suffix` as long as we can go.

Once done, we can return `res` :)

```cpp
struct Trie {
    int pos = -1;
    string fullWord = "";
    Trie *children[26] = {};
};

class WordFilter {
public:
    Trie *root = new Trie(), *curr;
    int res;

    void dfs(Trie *root, string suffix) {
        // updating res everytime we encounter a word end with a word that matches our suffix
        if (root->pos != -1 && 0 == root->fullWord.compare(root->fullWord.size() - suffix.size(), suffix.size(), suffix)) res = max(res, root->pos);
		// checking all the existing children
        for (auto child: root->children) {
            if (child) dfs(child, suffix);
        }
    }

    WordFilter(vector<string>& words) {
        // populating our trie
        for (int i = 0, lmt = words.size(); i < lmt; i++) {
            string word = words[i];
            curr = root;
            for (char c: word) {
                c -= 'a';
                if (!curr->children[c]) curr->children[c] = new Trie();
                curr = curr->children[c];
            }
            curr->pos = i;
            curr->fullWord = word;
        }
    }

    int f(string prefix, string suffix) {
        curr = root;
        // finding matching words
        for (char c: prefix) {
            c -= 'a';
            curr = curr->children[c];
        }
        // resetting res
        res = -1;
        // checking suffix
        dfs(curr, suffix);
        return res;
    }
};
```

