solutions.content:
Please take note how I create the Trie in the below example:

word: "google", index 0;
google, elgoog(reverse) -> TrieNode: g - e - o - l - o - g - g - o - l - o - e - g(Intersect google and elgoog(reverse))

word: "gogle", index 1:
gogle, elgog(reverse) -> TrieNode: g - e - o - l - g - g - l - o - e - g

As the TrieNode class is defined as below:
```
    class TrieNode{
        TrieNode[] children;
        int val;
        TrieNode(){
            val = 0;
            children = new TrieNode[26];
            return;
        }
    }
```
We can easily update the val (max weight) when we build the Trie

Now how to search with the prefix and suffix, For instance, we want to search "goog", "le"
we build the search string by interset the prefix and suffix(reverse), eg:
"goo", "el"(reversed)  -> "geolo\*g\*"
so we will search "geolo\*g\*" in the trie in which "*" could match any word. it will help to save a lot time with only linear time searching the TrieNode with O(length of prefix + length of suffix), and avoid to traverse any possible word to get the maximum weight. 

```
class WordFilter {
    class TrieNode{
        TrieNode[] children;
        int val;
        TrieNode(){
            val = 0;
            children = new TrieNode[26];
            return;
        }
    }

    TrieNode root = null;
    public WordFilter(String[] words) {
        root = new TrieNode();
        int idx = 0;
        for(String word : words){
            int low = 0;
            int high = word.length() - 1;
            int len = word.length();
            TrieNode node = root;
            while(low < len){
                char ch1 = word.charAt(low++);
                if(node.children[ch1 - 'a'] == null){
                    node.children[ch1 - 'a'] = new TrieNode();
                }
                node = node.children[ch1 - 'a'];
                node.val = idx;

                char ch2 = word.charAt(high--);
                if(node.children[ch2 - 'a'] == null){
                    node.children[ch2 - 'a'] = new TrieNode();
                }
                node = node.children[ch2 - 'a'];
                node.val = idx;
            }
            idx++;
        }
        return;
    }

    public int f(String prefix, String suffix) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
