The basic idea behind the solution is to create all the possible prefix and suffix combinations for each of the words given. In this way, in our find function we only need to check if that particular (prefix,suffix) combination exists in our list of combinations. 

I have used python dictionary to store all the possible combinations.

```
class WordFilter:

    def __init__(self, words: List[str]):
        self.pre={}
        for n,word in enumerate(words):
            for j in range(len(word)-1,-1,-1):
                for k in range(len(word)):
                    letter=word[j:]+"#"+word[:k+1]
                    self.pre[letter]=n

    def f(self, prefix: str, suffix: str) -> int:
        ans=suffix+"#"+prefix
        if self.pre.get(ans) is not None:
            return self.pre[ans]
        return -1
```

