solutions.content:
***This problem is solved using dynamic programming implemented using HashMap.*** 
* We created a class HashMap<List,Integer> to store the results.
* Each of the set of prefix and sufix is added in a list.
* As a standard dp way, before starting the operations we check if the solution already exists.
* We traverse words array from backwards and match prefix and suffix string with each string of the array.As soon as we encounter unequal values we break from the inner for loop.
* flag variable is keeping track of whether both suffix and prefix matches.
* If flag is true, we store result in map and return the ans.
* If we come to the end of the program, we store the value in the map and return -1.

**Code**
```
class WordFilter 
{
    String[] word;
    Map<List<String>,Integer> map=new HashMap<>();

    public WordFilter(String[] words) 
	{
        word=words;
	}

    public int f(String pre, String suff)
    {
        List<String> list=new ArrayList<>();
        list.add(pre);list.add(suff);

        //implemented dp
        if(map.containsKey(list))
            return map.get(list);

        int ans=-1;

        for(int i=word.length-1;i>=0;i--)
        {
            String str=word[i];
            boolean flag=true;

            //if prefix or suffix is longer than str
             if(pre.length()>str.length() || suff.length()>str.length())
                 continue;

            //to check prefix
            for(int j=0;j<pre.length();j++)
            {
                if(pre.charAt(j)!=str.charAt(j))
                {
                    flag=false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            //to check suffix 
            for(int j=suff.length()-1,k=str.length()-1;j>=0 && flag;)
            {
                if(suff.charAt(j--)!=str.charAt(k--))
                {
                    flag=false;
                    break;
                }
            }


             if(flag)
             {
               map.put(list,i);
               return i;
             }

        }
        map.put(list,ans);
        return ans;
    }
}

