Got here after thinking about many workarounds. Finally this worked. 

What I simply did is stored the answer for every possible {prefix,suffix} pair that can have a match in our dictionary. This makes my find function to give answer in O(1).       {:))
```
class WordFilter {
    String[] dict;
    Map<String,Integer> dp;

    public WordFilter(String[] words) {
        this.dict = words;
        this.dp = new HashMap<>();

        String pref, suf;
        for(int i=0;i<words.length;i++){            
            for(int j = 0;j<words[i].length()+1;j++){
                for(int k = words[i].length();k>-1;k--){ 

                    pref = words[i].substring(0,j);
                    suf = words[i].substring(k);

                    this.dp.put(pref+"/"+suf,i);
                }
            }   
        }
    }

    public int f(String prefix, String suffix) {
        if(this.dp.containsKey(prefix+"/"+suffix))
            return this.dp.get(prefix+"/"+suffix);
        return -1;

    }
}
